 debounce(func, wait) - A debounced version of the original function `func` that only runs after `wait` milliseconds have elapsed since the last time it was called.
```javascript
const debounce = (func, wait = 500) => {
  let timeout;

  return function(...args) {
    const context = this;
    const later = () => {
      clearTimeout(timeout);
      timeout = null;
      func.apply(context, args);
    };

    clearTimeout(timeout);

    if (timeout === null) {
      func.apply(context, args);
    } else {
      timeout = setTimeout(later, wait);
    }
  };
};

const log = console.log;
const debouncedLog = debounce(log);

document.addEventListener('keyup', debouncedLog);

// Press any key multiple times, you'll see the log message only after 500ms of inactivity
```
In this example, we've created a debounced version of the `console.log` function called `debouncedLog`. When the `keyup` event fires, `debouncedLog` is called. The actual `console.log` function will only execute after 500ms (the `wait` time) of no `keyup` events being fired.
